WEBVTT

00:00.100 --> 00:01.900
Previously on "Ghost Whisperer..."

00:02.100 --> 00:03.174
What do the shadows
want with my son?

00:03.208 --> 00:05.357
Whatever they are,
wherever they live,

00:05.391 --> 00:08.887
These shadows are very
interested in ghost children.

00:08.921 --> 00:10.768
Bedford. What are you doing here?

00:10.803 --> 00:13.218
Remember this...
nothing is what it seems.

00:13.252 --> 00:15.774
Trust nothing, and no one.

00:15.808 --> 00:17.954
Carl, what's going on?

00:17.989 --> 00:19.294
I sense them around me sometimes

00:19.328 --> 00:21.831
And I'll suddenly
feel so confused.

00:21.832 --> 00:23.084
You mean the shadows.

00:23.118 --> 00:25.663
It's like they're
getting inside my head.

00:30.964 --> 00:33.108
I could change my mind,

00:33.143 --> 00:35.653
As long as I don't let go, right?

00:38.471 --> 00:41.282
I'm going to leave it here.

00:47.679 --> 00:49.088
I know.

00:49.122 --> 00:50.627
But it's a...

00:50.661 --> 00:52.736
Sacrifice, like you said.

00:52.771 --> 00:54.446
See?

00:58.132 --> 01:00.174
Checkmate.

01:00.208 --> 01:02.850
Uh, hey. Sorry, buddy,

01:02.888 --> 01:03.891
But, um, we gotta go.

01:03.925 --> 01:05.263
It's OK. I won.

01:05.297 --> 01:06.801
Cool.

01:06.835 --> 01:07.838
Who you playing?

01:07.873 --> 01:10.084
Just Carl. He's teaching me.

01:10.118 --> 01:12.226
Carl? Yeah. You know,

01:12.260 --> 01:14.167
The watcher.

01:14.202 --> 01:16.912
Right.

01:23.539 --> 01:25.380
The details are impressive.

01:25.414 --> 01:27.959
My father collected stuff.

01:27.993 --> 01:29.097
Obviously.

01:29.131 --> 01:30.334
There's a ton more.

01:30.369 --> 01:32.076
I'm helping Gale
sell her dad's house.

01:32.110 --> 01:34.017
Yeah. He passed away last year.

01:34.051 --> 01:36.358
I'm so sorry. Thank you.

01:36.392 --> 01:39.503
So you think any of this
junk is worth anything?

01:39.537 --> 01:41.510
Everything is to somebody.

01:41.545 --> 01:43.385
Oh.

01:43.419 --> 01:46.496
Oh, it's my boyfriend.

01:46.530 --> 01:48.670
Excuse me.

01:48.704 --> 01:50.476
Hey, Kyle.

01:50.511 --> 01:52.716
Yeah, I'm at the
antique store now.

01:52.750 --> 01:54.354
You did?

01:54.388 --> 01:56.058
2 bedrooms, really?

01:56.092 --> 01:57.327
She and her boyfriend
are moving to the city.

01:57.362 --> 02:00.269
He's apartment hunting.
Well, when will we know?

02:00.303 --> 02:02.541
Ok, I'll keep my
fingers crossed, too.

02:02.575 --> 02:03.944
Yeah. Love you.

02:06.388 --> 02:07.623
Everything OK?

02:07.658 --> 02:09.530
Yeah, yeah, sorry.

02:09.564 --> 02:11.436
Um, it's just...

02:11.470 --> 02:13.976
It's a lot to process, you know?

02:14.010 --> 02:16.251
Selling my dad's house
and moving in with Kyle.

02:16.285 --> 02:17.988
Both of which my dad
would have hated.

02:18.023 --> 02:19.727
He didn't like your boyfriend?

02:19.762 --> 02:21.133
No, not really.

02:21.167 --> 02:24.108
And he especially did not like
the idea of us living together.

02:24.143 --> 02:25.111
He was pretty old school.

02:25.146 --> 02:27.317
But we waited,
6 months after he died,

02:27.352 --> 02:28.387
You know?

02:28.421 --> 02:30.126
Life goes on, right?

02:30.160 --> 02:32.432
It does. Ok, well,

02:32.466 --> 02:33.668
Why don't you just give me a call

02:33.703 --> 02:35.072
When you want to come see
the rest of the stuff?

02:35.108 --> 02:37.213
I will.

02:37.247 --> 02:40.755
I just hope my dad
can rest in peace,

02:40.789 --> 02:42.260
You know?

02:44.934 --> 02:46.772
Poor girl.

02:46.806 --> 02:49.213
She's still grieving. Yeah.

02:49.247 --> 02:52.388
But she's in love,
so I'm sure it'll be fine

02:52.422 --> 02:54.326
Once they get settled in.

02:56.300 --> 02:59.507
Oh, come on.

03:05.054 --> 03:07.957
"over my dead body"?

03:07.991 --> 03:09.891
Let me guess...

03:09.926 --> 03:12.159
Gale's dad.

03:12.193 --> 03:15.360
So much for resting in peace.

